:> :
:> :Thanks for that ;-)
:> :
:> :Ok, is that using raw searches of all primes in the range, random stabs
:> :or some form of cryptographic method?
:>  
:> None of the above. This is using either the Quadratic Sieve or the General
:> Number Field Sieve.
:> 
:
:Do you know of any other method?

Yes, but they are less efficient: ECM, SPAR/Seysen's method (and variations)
both run in sub-exponential time. P-1, Pollard Rho, Squfof all run in time
O(N^1/4). Ditto for P+1 and Bach/Shallit's cyclotomic methods. The
exponential methods are not very useful. ECM is not very useful if your
prime factors exceed 50 digits (largest factor found is 42 digits).

